      "title": "Cloud Gallery: High-Performance PHP Cloud Storage Gateway",
      "description": "Stratum is an enterprise-grade, lightweight Cloud Storage Gateway built in PHP that seamlessly bridges legacy on-premise applications with modern cloud object storage providers. By implementing a highly optimized PSR-7 compatible streaming architecture, Stratum solves the memory bottleneck typically associated with PHP file handling, allowing petabyte-scale data transfers with minimal memory footprints. It features a robust multi-provider adapter pattern supporting AWS S3, Google Cloud Storage, and Azure Blob, local Redis-backed metadata caching for sub-millisecond directory listings, and resilient chunked parallel uploads. This gateway enables organizations to modernize their storage infrastructure without rewriting legacy codebase dependencies, significantly reducing egress costs and operational complexity.",
